|CKBGuild Emotes|000

|CK0Guild emotes are social actions reserved for active members of a guild.
They behave like standard feelings: they can have untargeted, targeted, and
free-text forms, work in rooms, and can be used through guild channels that
support colon emotes.|000

|CKBPlayer commands|000
|CK0feelings guild - list every guild emote available to you
feelings guild <guild> - list emotes for one of your guilds
feelings guild <guild> <prefix> - filter that guild's list
semote <emote> - preview each supported form
emoteapropos guild [<guild>] <text> - search guild emote messages
random [<player>] - invoke a random available global or guild emote|000

|CK0A guild emote stops working immediately if you leave the guild or if that
guild's abilities become inactive. Seeing the result of an emote does not
grant access to use it.|000

|CKBArchitect commands|000
|CK0addemote -guild <guild> <name> [<rule>]
showemote -guild <guild> <name>
rmemote -guild <guild> <name> [<rule>]|000

|CK0The guild name is matched case-insensitively against the configured guild
list. Guild emotes use the standard addemote rule grammar, messages, preview,
and optional variable-emote redirects. They are stored separately from global
emotes and persist with the emote daemon. New names must not collide with a
global emote, another guild's emote, or an available command.|000

|CK0Use |YKBshowemote -guild|CK0 before editing or removing a definition.
Omitting |YKB-guild|CK0 operates on the global emote with that name, not the
guild definition.|000

|WKBSee also: |YKBaddemote, emotes, emoteapropos, feelings, random, rmemote,
semote, showemote|000

